Officers discovered the perlemoen at a house in the area following a tip-off earlier this week. CAPE TOWN - Police in Malmesbury are looking into the seizure of abalone worth R500,000. Officers discovered the perlemoen at a house in the area following a tip-off earlier this week. A 74-year-old man has been taken in for questioning but has not been arrested. The police's Noloyiso Rwexana said: “Upon their arrival, they seized the abalone. No one has been arrested at this stage. The investigation is still ongoing.” There have been at least five multi-million abalone busts by police and government officials in the Western Cape since December. (Edited by Mihlali Ntsabo)